message:
StackPilot major rewrite.

Used a ridiculously iterative process with ChatGPT to create this website. I found the best way to make it work for me personally is making the website as modular as possible that way ChatGPT can focus on small chunks of code rather than processing a whole website at once. I've also got ChatGPT to save a audit checklist for every page that it checks against with every page and we continue to add/remove things as we learn more together.

message:
data-xfer: Created scripts to convert JSON <=> Apex

Since Apex doesn't have a great solution for multiline strings I was having trouble changing JSON to Apex code and vice versa (e.g. figuring out what is wrong with a given JSON string in Apex code). So I used ChatGPT to create two bash scripts to accept input via stdin and print convert the input to the other format. It was hard getting the formatting correct (without installing the jq command), so when JSON is created from an Apex code snippet, it allows the user to load a webpage that automatically displays the formatted json text.
